caption: The old owners were cash only, these guys aren't. They opened just before the pandemic hit. With super safe pandemic friendly ordering, delicious food, wonderful cocktails, and lovely staff, it's well worth your time to dine with them!
Absolutely delicious! Food was amazing and so were the cocktails. We'll definitely be back.
Very fresh, very tasty oysters, and white wine.  The young owner always keeps a natural smile and the service attitude is very good.
Great old fashioned. Even better fisherman's  stew loved the spicy chorizo in the broth. Finished cleaning the plate with a baguette. The oysters were very fresh. Can't wait to come back here.

Amazing service, cocktails on point, and food to die for.  My fiance, brother and I stopped in here for dinner last night and ordered a bunch of things to share.  For cocktails he got the Gowanus Sunset and I got the Citlali - both drinks were very tasty and went down quick (too quick).  My favorite thing we ordered was the Fisherman's Stew with Grilled Lobster (photo below). We also ordered the Gowanus Plateau: oysters from Maine and NY, clams from Maine, shrimp cocktail, 1/2 lobster tail chilled with tarragon alioli and Main Uni. All of the seafood was super fresh and delicious.  I loved their migonette sauce and fresh horseradish to go with the oysters.  Everything was so good we didn't stop there- we went on to the Kale salad- super fresh and light, clam toast was incredible and I wanted a whole loaf of bread to soak up the sauce.  We also ordered Thai curry mussels with chorizo and the fisherman's stew with grilled lobster.  All of the sauces were amazing and made each bite enjoyable.  To end the meal we shared the chocolate mouse - I'm not a dessert person but this is by far the best dessert i've had - not too sweet or heavy (see photo).
Love love love this place! Just had Fristo Misto tonight.

The best seafood in NYC.  PERIOD.  Challenge me to a duel to prove otherwise. Pistols at noon? You’re on.   The Charred Squid Hash is the single best brunch item going.  Outrageously good.  Flavors for days.  Constantly rotating oyster selection.  Freshest of the fresh lobster rollls, clam rolls and crab rolls.  Butternut squash soup with shrimp! Every single menu item is worth its own review.  Great outdoor space.  And a staff that truly cares about COVID protocols. Keeping everyone safe whether indoor or out.  I love you, Littleneck.
Great food and amazing service. The NE Clam Chowder is up there with the best I've eaten.
Great place to eat! Loved the oysters and the service was impeccable. We will be going back again. I'm hoping they still have indoor dining when we do.
This place is awesome
Everything was fresh and delicious!! I loved the sea urchin with jalapeño oil. Love you guys!!

This HAS to be one of the best brunch places in NYC. It checks off all the boxes: really good food, great ambiance, extremely nice people, good prices.  Even if you don't like seafood, which is a specialty here, you would enjoy the lemon ricotta pancakes and the fried chicken. They also make really good fries.  Every time I've been here, the vibe is just right -- good people (shout out to Elisa!) and good music (always reggae).  The drinks are SUPER well balanced.  My only regret is not having enough stomachs to eat all the things.  Please come support this amazing gem of a restaurant -- I am always thankful that the dishes they have here exist for me to enjoy. In these crazy times, flavors in the food you eat create joy that is so needed.  What I've ordered(still working through the entire menu!)  Bloody caesar drink (Bloody Mary with a clam) Spicy tequila sunrise Shrimp and grits (best I've EVER had and so will you. Prove me wrong) Squid hash (fantastic) Lemon ricotta pancakes (best I've ever had. Prove me wrong again) Daily oysters (always good) Lobster roll
love this place, the food the beverages and rhe hospitality is truly amazing!

I thought I’d try a new place so I went on a Saturday at lunchtime. It was empty. My mom and I sat down and ordered burgers 1 medium and 1 well done.  Twenty minutes later the waitress brought flavorless coleslaw and a pickle.  After what seemed like forever but was 30 minutes I went to put $$ in the meter and my mom asked what’s taking so long with the food. The waitress replied, “well we’re cooking it the way you wanted.” My mom owned a deli and I’ve worked as a waitress for many years. It doesn’t take anywhere near a half hour to cook a burger and if a customer asks you what’s wrong blaming them Isn’t the best way. We took our things and left. Worst diner experience. No wonder their a dying breed.
Food is great 😊
Love this place. First time trying outdoor dining, and it was great. Oysters were excellent as was the clam roll. Everyone is super nice as well. Continues to be one of our favorite restaurants.
This spot is worth giving a shot. They serve large portions for fair rates. Constantly well organized and with awesome character. Will come visit again.

This restaurant is my number one site.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to that place. when  I want to go to a proper lunch, this restaurant comes right away to my mind. excellent and varied  food and a large list of dishes.trained staff members, and agreeable ambience. Also, the charge is honest. I sent my friends to this restaurant with no hesitation.
The freshest seafood prepared simple enough to really let the main ingredient stand out, and yet creative enough to keep you coming back for more!!
This place is absolutely bangin.  Meaning it is super good.  Definitely one of the best lobster rolls in the city.  Definitely check this place out for some solid eats.
Fun atmosphere, delicious food and friendly staff. Best oysters in Brooklyn and loved the lobster roll. Highly recommend!
Great oysters! Very  special!!

This place is everything! I could talk about the perfect vibes, the music, the impeccable service, but let me talk about how unexpectedly amazing the food is! Without a doubt this is out new jam. Highest recommendation.
This spot is worth a try. They have large portions for affordable prices. Regularly well organized and with awesome vibes. I highly recommend this place.

The food and service is pretty good. However their pricing is outrageous.   They charge nearly the same price as Pearl’s in the West Village, yet only a 1/3rd of three meat. Not sure how they justify their pricing, considering they are in a much worse neighborhood. It’s very similar to Luke’s lobster roll, yet charging twice the amount Luke’s charges.  We also had a clam roll which only had 6 clams. You need to order two rolls to have enough clams for one good roll.  I will say the lobster and clams were cooked perfectly, firm yet quite moist, and their Cole slaw is excellent.  Lastly, their fresh donuts are excellent.
Nice place with good seafood. Just as it is
Nice quiet little place. Food was good. I ordered the mussels with fries. They were very tasty.
This spot gives first-rate service as well as delicious meals. My favourite restaurant ever. The food arrived fast and the prices were affordable. Recommended.
I went there two days in a row
Cosy space, friendly staff. Good oysters, though food is mixed.

I go with my wife to this place quite often! This is the best place to have a bite.  I visit this place regularly. The food is fantastic, the staff members are helpful and the charge is decent. I like being in this spot over a good meal.
Food was good....not great, friendly staff but nothing special...not even worth going back to. They only accept cash so that's a pain.
Best Bloody Mary and fine oysters!
Pretty great little restaurant tucked between a few other nice small places. Seafood was very good and the staff accommodating

Cozy little place that we just happened to stumble upon. Glad we did because the cocktails and the food were great and they have very friendly and attentive service. The oysters are so fresh! They are cash only, but luckily there's an ATM tucked away in towards the back.
Owner was on beat bobby flay and won with his clam belly sandwhich. Go here and get that! So good. Pricey though and cash only

The quality is just not there. The seafood just seemed not so fresh, and efforts to cover it up with sauces and intriguing preparations can’t overcome that. The lobster in the lobster roll was particularly disappointing... a bit “fishy” and rubbery. Maybe I should have tried the oysters people seem so fond of?
(Translated by Google) Perfect  (Original) Perfecto
Really great seafood. But we were a bit surprised that they only took cash on a 200+ bill.
Cash only , kinda pricey for me. , staff and bartender were nice and super hot  , its like they hired models or something
Amazing spot for great seafood
Excellent oyster selection, and really enjoyed the Portuguese fish stew.

When you're trying something and your only natural response is a single loud expletive, you know it's good. That happened multiple times to our entire group. Chef Nick Williams aka Heavy Cream Nick is a culinary artist. The food was delicious and poison sizes were great. No wonder he beat Bobby Flay. I recommend trying the LN Burger and getting the Broccolinni as an appetizer.
Great oysties, Free Smoke is a great cocktail choice. Dynamite interior
Food is superb
Cozy atmosphere. Delicious food. Great ambiance.

I loved the crab roll. I went out of my comfort zone on this one, as I'm not a sandwich person, and it paid off. Little bread, lots of crab, and fresh simple toppings made this a memorable meal. The PEI oysters of the day were both very fresh and delicious too.
Amazing
Amazing and delicious oysters. Great atmosphere. Everything perfect.

Fresh seafood galore on 4th Avenue in Brooklyn. Their raw bar options are great and accompanied by classic, boozy cocktail options. If you are craving the classic seafood tower, oysters on the half shelf, or fish and chips  accompanied by a polite, accommodating staff this is the perfect place.
Their happy hour oysters are $1.50 rather than the typical $1, but SO worth it.
Food and service were great. Taking one star off for the horrible bathroom.
Everything on the menu is delicious and the drinks go down easy. Get the clams.
Hostess is like a dear old friend of the family.

Oh my gosh. Left my heart here! Fresh oysters daily. A dive bar with a very sophisticated vibe. Grits and shrimp was absolutely amazing I loved it. Ginger beer is also very pleasant. It made our trip to New York.
Great place. Friendly service.  Really fresh seafood. The whole belly clam sandwich is worth the trip.  Only hitch is that they're cash only.
Fair prices and wonderful food/service.  We really enjoyed the ambiance as well
Pricey, service was good, drinks are good.
Go with a friend/date, get two glasses of white, one dozen oysters, and chase with the burger. One of my favorite meals in Brooklyn.
Very consistent. Always a pleasure to have dinner there.
Excellent seafood with a new twist.
Fantastic seafood fantastic service
This restaurant they make good food and they have a big space tables chairs if you have money friends have fun.

Great meal.  Service was lovely and very accommodating for my girlfriend who has a gluten allergy. Personally I had the chowder and the burger, both which are excellent.  She loved the oysters she had, the grilled kale salad and the Portuguese Stew.  Both of us will gladly head there again when in the area!
Really good food#
Love their lobster sandwich

Amazing place.  All dishes are incredible; well paired, simple yet surprising. One must get the lamb and clam stew! It’s to die for. Littleneck has really nice vibe and ambiance. All around a lovely place.
Pretentious staff in dive joint
Amazing seafood and friendly faces!

Went to this restaurant couple of time now and every time I get out saying "why aren't we going there once a week?". The service is always perfect. The food is fresh and delicious. Perfect for a date night, family reunion or a lovely evening with friends. Just over all a great place to visit. Great time, fresh sea food, solid drinks...why am I writing this? Hunny grab your coat! See you guys!

Incredibly tasty food, great flavors combination, even of the sides. very fresh, you can taste the quality of the ingredients. We were full but got tempted by the description of the doughnuts, although those are rarely a hit with me - those were amazing, must try.
The clams and lamb entree was amazing! So was everything else we ordered.
Best Bloody, amazing brunch and dinner. Squid hash is a must.
Dollar Oyster Happy Hour. Lovely space, great staff. What more needs to be said?

Beautifully cooked skate, a delicious Provencal stew, and a very tasty soft shell crab! You can never go wrong with the seafood at Little Neck. We also had a snow pea shoot salad that lacked some zing in the dressing. I prefer to eat here in the evenings when it's quieter. They do make a great brunch too. Their shrimp and grits are some of the best I've ever had. Dollar oysters in the afternoon are good too!
Great softshell crab!!!
Great food and wine plus a wonderful atmosphere. Would be 5 starts but the cash only payment is a little inconvienient.
New England fried clams (with bellies) and steamers, oysters and clams, situated a sand dollar toss from the fabled Gowanus Canal.  Mm-mm good.  Bring cash.
Pretty decent seafood, reasonable price. It's a go-to if that's your thing!
Real tasty food, great service.
Seafood yum
Awesome food and wonderful service. Thank you very much !
All smiles eating the delicious ricotta pancakes and a lobster roll for brunch
The lobster roll with fries was delicious
Pricey but tasty. The salmon tar tar was divine. Great cocktails. Cozy atmosphere.

Some of the best oysters around. Every batch so fresh and flavorful. Happy hour on oysters is $1.25 but I recommend trying the others too. The staff is great and the bar tender is really nice and friendly. Came here for the first time after living in the area for 6 years and will now make this a regular spot.

A neighborhood GEM.  Fresh tasty seafood.  Service is super friendly.  Cash only and they have a great happy hour special on food and drinks.  Favorite must try items, grilled lobster tail, pea shoot salad, Thai spiced mussels, and Portuguese seafood stew.
Super delicious seafood! Raw oysters were so delicious! Highly recommend it for fresh seafood.
Excellent oysters!
Best oysters. Great selection!
Delicious food, attentive service, and drinks, including wine from Maine! Had the clam chowder, spätzle, mussels with chorizo, kale salad, and halibut, each one well flavored and presented.

Service slow, my friends burger was extremely salty, lobster roll was ridiculously small, the doughnuts we ordered were not cooked all the way through and at the end they say it’s cash only (no sign anywhere at no point we were told of this until when we were about to pay). At this point there are better options other places for these high prices. No plans of going back anytime soon.
Very delicious and very well displayed food

Food was awesome loved the Wiley oysters omg so good. But horrible when my bill came it was only cash n I had to leave my date to go look for a atm. Who walks around with like $150 in cash now a days. Was alittle embarrassed.
Really nice unpretentious place with great seafood dishes and also a burger. Cozy and homie. Loved it.
Delicious oystiZ & seafood Cash ONLY !
Not cheap, excellent food.

If you are in Gowanus, you must try the deliciously smoky cocktail Free Smoke. The smoke of the mescal and juicy pineapple goes perfect with the brine of fresh oysters and the oh-so-yummy Portuguese Stew!! Oh, and they offer a sidecar of draft beer… yes please! The 21ST Amendment Hell or High Watermelon is a summer favorite of mine! This is definitely a fun place for a date with your fellow seafood lover. Can’t wait to check out their brunch menu at the newest location in Williamsburg!

Happy hour at its best. $5 drafts and $1.25 oysters. Clams are always $12 for a dozen. Tonight's specialty was Beau Soleil from New Brunswick. Super fresh seafood. Try the mussels and the steamers. Bar staff was super friendly too. Only thing that could make his place better is if it were on the ocean and there was live music in the evening. This was my first time, but I will be back.
Loved the food. Poor wine list. Then came the bill. No credit cards accepted! Lucky we had some cash because we don't use ATMs.
Surprisingly good pancakes

Great place for fresh seafood.  Love their clam po boy, which is overloaded with yummy fried clams.  They make very good cocktails.  And of course, oysters.  They have a great selection and if you get their for happy hour great prices.
Lemon ricotta pancakes are stellar.

This is purely on service and ridiculous policies because I wasn't actually able to get any food from here. I tried to first call in an order and was told they don't take orders over the phone. So I walked over there and tried to order, but the hostess said that they only take orders online on Saturday nights because it's busy  ... on Seamless, their prices are $2 more expensive per menu item ... Hostess was rude and not courteous. Hey management, try not to bilk your customers for not eating in the restaurant. Complete disappointment.

Unexpected in a great way!! First time here and came in on a whim. The wait staff was very friendly and attentive. Drinks were perfectly balanced...(Yes, there are some places that mess up a basic vodka & cranberry). We ordered several items off the menu and we were not disappointed. The littleneck clams tasted fresh and clean, the shrimp cocktail was excellent. For me the star was the clam roll...it tasted amazing and was stuffed full. I highly recommend it! Also the crab cake was light and flavorful. Then dessert came...YUM...these little donuts, made fresh, hot soft inside, crispy outside, with a Jameson infused whipped cream. I enjoyed the entire experience and will be visiting again bringing friends & family. I hope my next experience will be as great as my first, for my expectations are quite high now, so many places fall off because the quality goes down. Keep up the great work to the front and back of house.

The food was good and the bartender made a killer martini. I think what stood out about Littleneck overall was the service.  Very friendly and made us fee super comfortable and like they really enjoyed having us there.  We ate mostly raw bar items. It was all great.  Expensive, but for the quality worth it.

Never seated.  Arrived with my wife and daughter.  There were plenty of open tables.  Was told in a condescending tone it would be a 45 minute wait.  I left my cellphone number.  They never called.  We obviously did not fit their upscale hipster demographic.  Felt unwelcome.  I wonder if the human rights commission, or even the local paper, would send testers.  In response to the rude response from the owner, I was reminded of my family's absolutely horrible experience at Littleneck from about a year ago, by the similar, but milder, rudeness I experienced yesterday at Insa.  That review was similar, but milder.  What we experienced at Littleneck has stuck with me for all this time.  This review is under my name, and I am a real person who, together with my family, was really insulted by our treatment.  The condescending tone still shows, even when the owner tries to respond:  I didn't "think" this happened to us.  It happened.  My wife talked me out of filing a discrimination complaint.  We couldn't decide whether it was age (my take), race (my wife's take) or just that we weren't hip enough (my daughter's take).
Dan the bartender is amazing

Poor service, good oysters and wine. I wouldn't come here for a full meal, but it's a nice place to stop in and have some raw oysters, fries, and a couple of drinks. The bartenders and servers are very inattentive and turn you away prematurely if you come in before their dinner service starts. They do let you sit if you stress that you're just ordering from the raw bar.
Cozy spot with great seafood. The clam roll is fantastic.
Enjoyable atmosphere and good place to meet with close friends - you don't have to raise your voice to hear each other. Food was decent. Service was great.
Love it
Food was delicious, but portions were extremely small and service was slow.
Great food, good beer, great time.
Great food cozy ambiance.
After work go to the bar with your coworker, have a beer and the Thai mussles to share. Best place to end the day.
Great happy hour. The waitress Karen was so prompt and helpful. My favorite bar in Park slope
This place is great. Excellent wine/cider/beer by the glass. Really killer raw bar and the clam roll is what's up. Thanks for being here!
The best chicken and waffles/burger/oysters/service/and the most attractive staff in all of NYC. I moved to LA from New York, and every time I come back, I eat at Littleneck at least twice. No joke.
Amazing brunch. Lemon ricotta pancakes is all I have to say. Oysters are really good, nicely priced. Clam roll is awesome as well!
Fried clams.
Great clams!
Service was slow but food was excellent

The oysters and the drinks were good but the reason i gave it 2 stars was the service! . The place was light with ppl and it took forever for them to come around to ask for a 2nd drink to getting your check. Should have went to BK crab.

Great beer selection. I was very happy with my options here. Boardwalk fries are the best fries and theirs are so good that I had two orders. The decor is cool and eclectic. The service left much to be desired.

I ordered the roast beet sandwich, and it's like nobody ever even tried the thing before they put it on the menu. It's an open faced sourdough baguette, piled high with beets and a bit of arugula. There's literally no actual way to eat it. You can't cut sourdough bread with a butter knife, but the second you try to lift the thing, it just spills out everywhere. It was, no joke, the dumbest single meal item I've been served in my entire life. Boo.  (Guy working there was a total champ and remade it in a bowl, but still...)

Always delicious, Littleneck serves a hearty meal no matter what you order. Brunch is great with everything from the egg sandwich to the fried chicken and waffle on point. Tasty cocktails, too. Only been twice for dinner, but was equally impressed. Out of the way and thus less annoying than it would be for this level of food anywhere else. Littleneck rules!

decent enough bar, and good service, but if you're only going to come in for a couple of beers and and order of fries, expect some attitude from the bartender. also, I cannot justify $18 for a lobster roll...I don't care how good it is.

I visited Littleneck using Brokelyn's Beer Book with two friends. Visiting during their awkward time between brunch and dinner, we only ordered two sets fries to supplement our beer at the bar since the four other available food items were seafood. The service was decent and decor was nice. Lobster rolls will run you $18 but if you want a cheaper snack, the fries are amazing!
Beware! Food Poisoning! Clams not fresh and not cleaned properly. My whole family got sick!

I was disappointed with my last meal here - I ordered the scallop special for $21 and got three scallops. $7 each?! It was on the entree menu! I ordered steamers to supplement my meal which are difficult/fun to eat, but the portion was still lacking. I went home and ordered pizza.  Stick to this place for happy hour oysters ($1) and drafts (the wine menu is expensive). Also, dessert - every dessert I've had here is out of the this world. Who would have thought?!

I want to like this place more than I do. They have a decent happy hour ($1 oysters (shuckers choice) and $5 drafts), but wine is pricey. Unfortunately, the oysters weren't shucked terribly well -- lots of bits of shell. Burger, pie and salad were fine, but nothing really got me excited. The best thing about the place is the decor, it feels like you're really at the beach.

I came here for some oysters and steamers.  They were out of most of the menu even though it was only 7:30.  Service was incredibly slow.  I must have waited over an hour for the food, which was decent but not extraordinary.   The decor was a little over the top.  They had recently opened when I was there, so things may have improved as they  have worked out kinks.
This place is adorable. Fresh seafood-- get the lobster roll.
Okay food.  Overpriced oysters.
